  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Gallery Card Display Issue - Fix Card Body Visibility\n\nResolve the display problem where the gallery card body is not rendering correctly due to incorrect height inheritance from the parent gallery-card-link element.\n\nRequirements:\n- Investigate the CSS styles applied to `.gallery-card-link` and `.gallery-card-body` elements\n- Identify why `height: 100%` on `.gallery-card-link` is causing the card body to not display\n- Determine if the issue is related to parent container constraints or flex/grid layout conflicts\n- Implement a fix that allows the card body to display properly while maintaining intended layout structure\n- Consider alternative approaches such as:\n  - Using `min-height` instead of `height: 100%`\n  - Adjusting flex properties if using flexbox\n  - Modifying parent container constraints\n  - Using grid layout if more appropriate\n- Verify the fix works across different card content lengths and viewport sizes\n- Ensure clickable area of the gallery-card-link remains functional after the fix\n- Test in major browsers to ensure consistent rendering",
